          <h4>Bio</h2>
          <p>I am currently a PhD student in Machine Learning at Georgia Tech, advised by Prof. <a href="https://cs.stanford.edu/~diyiy/">Diyi Yang</a>, and a visiting researcher at the Stanford NLP Group. During my PhD, I have interned at Google AI working on Google Assistant and at Meta GenAI on pretraining for Llama 3 and 4.</p>
          <p>My research focuses on methods for rapidly adapting language technology to new domains and modalities. The goal is to make fundamental language technologies more robust and easier to adapt, so that they can be a foundation for innovation by a broader population. During my PhD, I have worked on the following topics:</p>
          <h6>Language, Dialect, and Domain Robustness</h6>
          <p>Developing methods to quickly adapt language technology to new &amp; diverse settings with little to no additional training data.
          <br/>
          [(<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2023.findings-acl.51/">ACL 2023a</a>), (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2501.11747">Meta 2025</a>)]</p>
          <h6>Social &amp; Cultural Factors in NLP</h6>
          <p>Understanding how human social systems inform and influence the performance of language technology for different user groups.
          <br/>
          [(<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2024.acl-long.853/">ACL 2024a</a>), (<a href="https://aclanthology.org/2024.findings-acl.241/">ACL 2024b</a>)]</p>
          <h6>Speech Processing &amp; Voice Assistants</h6>
<p>Evaluating and improving the ability for language models to assist users naturally and efficiently through spoken conversation.
          <br/>
          [(<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2410.02678">ACL 2025a</a>), (<a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2502.15919">ACL 2025b</a>)]</p>
          <br/>
          <p>Before my PhD, I was an engineer at <a href="https://techcrunch.com/2020/11/18/marissa-mayers-startup-launches-its-first-official-product-sunshine-contacts/">Sunshine AI</a> where I reported directly to <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/marissamayer/">Marissa Mayer</a> and performed research with Prof. <a href="https://web.stanford.edu/~jurafsky/">Dan Jurafsky</a>. I did my undergraduate degree at NYU Abu Dhabi, where I worked on lexical semantics and Arabic NLP advised by Prof. <a href="https://nyuad.nyu.edu/en/academics/divisions/science/faculty/nizar-habash.html">Nizar Habash</a>. In my free time, I enjoy running <a href="https://ultrarunning.com/calendar/runner/view/Will-Held-3e862fc8-7f94-11ec-8b7d-b606cb15cdaf">very</a> <a href="https://marathonguide.com/print/oakland-running-festival/results/?subevent=all&gender=all&age_group=all&page=1&limit=10&order_by=chip_time&order_dir=desc&year=2022&last_name=Held&first_name=William">long</a> <a href="https://www.athlinks.com/event/231440/results/Event/1004459/Course/2192874/Bib/3591">distances</a>.</p>
